The CD board would automatically waive linkage for all affordable housing units.

172
00:19:53,802 --> 00:20:01,104
So linkage is designed, it's set up as trust funds for police, fire, water, sewer, parks, and roads.

173
00:20:03,283 --> 00:20:17,837
And usually the money that goes in there is used by the city for projects that are off site that the idea being that every new unit and every new building adds to the burden on all of these departments.

174
00:20:18,378 --> 00:20:25,164
And you can't just make the last one that comes in, pay for the new thing that you need, but rather that they accumulate.

175
00:20:26,626 --> 00:20:31,911
By having everybody put some money in, it spreads the load around.

176
00:20:32,752 --> 00:20:36,976
Medford is the only community in Massachusetts that has this form of linkage.

177
00:20:37,036 --> 00:20:39,679
Some other communities have affordable housing linkage.

178
00:20:40,099 --> 00:20:43,303
